## Investigation Complete

**Issue**: #650 - CI broken on main: Deploy to staging
**Type**: BUG

### Assessment

| Metric | Value | Reasoning |
|--------|-------|-----------|
| Severity | HIGH | Both staging and production deploys are fully blocked |
| Complexity | LOW | Single file, two blocks to replace |
| Confidence | HIGH | Unambiguous error log pointing to exact failure |

### Root Cause

`appleboy/ssh-action@v1` downloads the `drone-ssh` binary from GitHub releases at runtime. The download URL `https://github.com/appleboy/drone-ssh/releases/download/v1.8.2` returned HTTP 504 six times in a row, causing exit code 4 before any SSH connection was made.

**Fix**: Replace both `appleboy/ssh-action@v1` usages in `.github/workflows/staging-pipeline.yml` with a two-step pattern: write the SSH key + `ssh-keyscan`, then invoke native `ssh` via a double-quoted heredoc. Ubuntu runners ship with OpenSSH — no binary download needed.

### Files to Modify

| File | Action |
|------|--------|
| `.github/workflows/staging-pipeline.yml:37-59` | REPLACE staging deploy step |
| `.github/workflows/staging-pipeline.yml:118-154` | REPLACE production deploy step |

